W: But we don’t have enough time to do it. As you know, 
we’re supposed to have lunch with Dad at one o’clock 
in the afternoon.  
M: Oh, I forgot about that. Then, how about putting 
together dinosaurs’ bones? It won’t take much time.
W: Okay, that’s a good idea.
M: All right, Mom.
